@NODE Todo
@TITLE "Finder`s future"

If I get feedback from you (and if I can be bothered), these are some of the
things I would like to see in Finder V3.00:

ｷ Option to turn off recursive searching.
ｷ Option to search multi-volumes.
ｷ Commodity support.
ｷ AppIcon support.
ｷ AppWindow support (i.e. drop a drawer to search).
ｷ Localisation (anybody want to translate for me?).
ｷ Use ReqTools for the About requester and a directory requester.
ｷ Option to save list produced to an ASCII file.
ｷ Option to print list produced.
ｷ Option to search any assign 'add's (e.g. if FONTS: points to more than one directory)
   Example-script:

      $VER:startup-sequence v39.29
      assign FONTS: SYS:Fonts
      assign FONTS: Work:Fonts ADD

   Currently, Finder would only search SYS:Fonts. If I can work out how to do it, it
   would also search Work:Fonts


These are some things I would like to put in, but only if someone pays me:

ｷ Option to automatically search LhA/LZX files for the file pattern
  (VERY difficult to do without LhA routines!).
ｷ Option to search individual files for string patterns.
  (Also VERY difficult to do (Well, I think so!))

If you would like to get involved with updating Finder, please contact me at the
address in the @{"Contacting the Author" link Author} section.

@ENDNODE

